To get the full guide it would be best to go to the site https://pytorch.org/.

Setting up on a windows machine I will be going with the cuda support as well as with andanconda
**Note that it is required to have at least window 7 or higher. As well as only supported with the python language. 

First download anaconda from there website https://www.anaconda.com/download
This will give python as will as the pip install. This also install many other usefull libray's like numpy and sklearn. 
** They will try to get you to sign up with an email, but you can just skip it with the button right bellow. 

after it is downloaded open the anaconda prompt and install the commands
**note that this may take some time go make a sandwhich. 
pip install torch
pip install numpy
pip install pandas
pip install sklearn
pip install matplotlib
